Dynamic XPath is used to locate web elements whose attributes change dynamically
every time the page loads. It uses functions like contains() or starts-with() to create flexible locators.

Dynamic XPath ek aisa XPath hota hai jo dynamic (change hone wale) elements ko locate karne ke liye use hota hai.

Bahut websites me element ka id ya attribute har page load par change ho jata hai.
Aise case me exact XPath kaam nahi karta, isliye dynamic XPath use karte hain.

Example of Dynamic Element
HTML:
<input id="user_12345" type="text">

Next time page load hone par:

<input id="user_67890" type="text">

Agar hum likhen:

driver.findElement(By.xpath("//input[@id='user_12345']"));

To next time element locate nahi hoga.
-------------------
Dynamic XPath Solution
1️⃣ Using contains()
driver.findElement(By.xpath("//input[contains(@id,'user')]"));

➡️ Id change hone par bhi element locate ho jayega.

2️⃣ Using starts-with()
driver.findElement(By.xpath("//input[starts-with(@id,'user')]"));
3️⃣ Using text()
driver.findElement(By.xpath("//button[text()='Login']"));
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Why Dynamic XPath is Used
Dynamic elements handle karne ke liye
Page reload hone par attribute change hone par
Stable locator banane ke liye
